0.body: Welcome to the exciting yet secure game platform built based on Chia Blockchain Platform . This wiki intends to provide some basic information about nika.com. If you have any unanswered questions about nika.com, you could join our Discord server.
0.title: Introduction

1.body: Game in Nika is a form of play in predefined set of time which player try to guess some number which will appear at the end of the game, and will get the reward if their guess is correct.
1.title: Game Rules

10.body:
Confirmation means the Chia's block where the transaction happened is buried with another block. The more considerable the amount, the more confirmation is needed for transactions confirmed by the game. For any transaction below 1 XCH, ten confirmation is needed. For any transaction above or equal to 1 XCH, the following rules apply: minConfirmation = ((amountInMojo / 10000000000000) + 2) * 10
Divide operation executed as integer division, which means the result is floored.
10.title: 9. Transaction Confirmations

11.body: Anyone can repeatedly calculate every result in Nika games, but the result is always consistent. There's no way to know the outcome of future games, hence Provably Fair. As stated in the rules , a player must buy a ticket to participate in Nika games. Ticket purchasing happens in the Chia blockchain, which produces a unique Coin ID. So each game will have its own set of Coin IDs. To calculate the game result, one has to append all the Coin IDs for the said game (in hex format, with 0x prefix), then hash it with SHA-256. Take the hash result in decimal representation, and then: FirstNumber = First to the fourth character of the result. SecondNumber = Fifth to the eighth character of the result. ThirdNumber = Ninth to the twelfth character of the result. JackpotNumber = Thirteenth character of the result. Learn how to prove it here .
11.title: Provably Fair

12.body: Anyone could become a backer in Nika's game as long as they have at least 6000000000000 Mojo (6 XCH). As you may already guess, the amount of 6 XCH comes up from the sum of the prizes (excluding JackpotPrize). Backers guarantee the winner gets the compensation they deserve. For their committed XCH in each game, a backer would get the reward. All the backers would get a share of ticket sales of the game they backed. Share percentage can be seen at Ticket Sales Allocation . And that amount will be distributed among backers according to their contribution. Although, there is some game when ticket sales won't cover the amount of the prizes. If that happens, then backers committed amount would be cut proportionally according to their contribution. That means some eligible backers in the current game may be ineligible at the next game. The more eligible backers the game has, the more exciting the game would be, as it would increase the game's SlotPerNumber. And, since the game would not start when there is no eligible backer, we make sure there's always at least one backer around.

2.body: Each game in Nika lasted 120 minutes. Timezone used is UTC. There can't be two or more games running simultaneously. It's always one game at a given time.

20.body: Each game in Nika is declared profit when XCH collected from ticket sales is more than XCH given for the winner prize, and said loss otherwise. Note that the Jackpot prize is out of this equation since it has its prize pool. When the game is profit, here is the share percentage where the fund goes: 30% for site maintenance. 40% for the backers. 30% for the Jackpot Pool Prize.

5.body: Player is declared the winner if their ticket's number matches the game result. There is four types of a winner, FirstWinner, SecondWinner, ThirdWinner, and JackpotWinner. FirstWinner is whose ticket's 4-digit number matches FirstNumber. SecondWinner is whose ticket's 4-digit number matches SecondNumber. ThirdWinner is whose ticket's 4-digit number matches ThirdNumber. JackpotWinner is the FirstWinner whose ticket's 1-digit matches JackpotNumber. If the game's SlotPerNumber is more than one, it's possible to have multiple winners in each type. Since a player could buy more than one ticket, then it's possible for one player to declare as every winner type.
5.title: 4. Win Condition

6.body: FirstWinner would be rewarded 3000000000000 Mojo (3 XCH). SecondWinner would be rewarded 2000000000000 Mojo (2 XCH). ThirdWinner would be rewarded 1000000000000 Mojo (1 XCH). JackpotWinner would be rewarded by any XCH available in Jackpot Pool Prize. When there are multiple FirstWinner, SecondWinner, and ThirdWinner in one game, each of them would be rewarded the full amount according to their winning type. When there are multiple JackpotWinner in one game, the reward from Jackpot Pool Prize would be distributed equally among JackpotWinners. Every prize is immediately sent to the winner's payout address after the game end. At the end of each game, the jackpot pool prize is calculated first according to Ticket Sales Allocation , then distributed to the JackpotWinners for that game, if there are any.
6.title: 5. Prize

7.body: Each game needs at least one eligible backer to be started. When there is none, then the game will not start. Backer is declared eligible when they commit 6000000000000 Mojo (6 XCH) or more. Any profit or loss that happens in one game would be distributed according to their backing amount. Profit sharing reward immediately sent to backer's payout address after the game end. Backer would take loss sharing from their committed XCH after the game end. Withdrawal of committed XCH would be processed and sent to the backer's payout address after the game end. Backer's committed amount would be recalculated at the end of the game, so their eligibility may be changed in the next game.
7.title: 6. Backer

8.body: SlotPerNumber is calculated before the game starts and will not change until the game is finished. SlotPerNumber is calculated by dividing the game's backed amount by the total prize amount, which is 6000000000000 Mojo (6 XCH). If the divide operation has a remainder, it will be floored.
8.title: 7. SlotPerNumber

9.body: Reserved ticket is automatically created when a player purchases a ticket for the 4-digit number already bought up to the current game's SlotPerNumber. Reserved tickets would be used to purchase a ticket with the same number in the next games. Ticket purchasing from reserved tickets would be executed before the game. Coin ID used to calculate a game result for the ticket purchased by the reserved ticket is the Coin ID for the original transaction. Reserved ticket is sorted by the transaction height in the Chia blockchain. The smaller the height, the sooner it will be executed.
9.title: 8. Reserved Ticket
